’m thinking about whether to include a helper `method()` with comments, but maybe I won't. It seems I should check the dynamic call sites around lines 99 and 103, where `Method.invoke` is used. By manually invoking the handler, it looks like coverage will be recorded well, so I’m planning to write a new file instead of running tests.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_F4OHQ0khVfulc65nNChCETTe|fc_077ccfdcb7edf56f0169fefea15f60819caf2ff02651657e9c", "name": "write", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.jboss.interceptor/jboss-interceptor-core/2.0.0.CR1/src/test/java/org_jboss_interceptor/jboss_interceptor_core/InterceptorMethodHandlerTest.java", "content": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\npackage org_jboss_interceptor.jboss_interceptor_core;\n\nimport java.lang.reflect.Method;\n\nimport org.jboss.interceptor.builder.InterceptionModelBuilder;\nimport org.jboss.interceptor.proxy.InterceptorMethodHandler;\nimport org.jboss.interceptor.reader.ReflectiveClassMetadata;\nimport org.jboss.interceptor.spi.context.InvocationContextFactory;\nimport org.jboss.interceptor.spi.instance.InterceptorInstantiator;\nimport org.jboss.interceptor.spi.metadata.ClassMetadata;\nimport org.jboss.interceptor.spi.model.InterceptionModel;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\n\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\n\npublic class InterceptorMethodHandlerTest {\n\n    @Test\n    void invokesNonCandidateMethodOnTargetInstanceForDelegatingProxy() throws Throwable {\n        final InvocationTarget targetInstance = new InvocationTarget(\"target\");\n        final InterceptorMethodHandler handler = newHandler(targetInstance, InvocationTarget.class);\n        final Method equalsMethod = Object.class.getMethod(\"equals\", Object.class);\n\n        final Object result = handler.invoke(\n                new InvocationTarget(\"self\"),\n                equalsMethod,\n                equalsMethod,\n                new Object[] {targetInstance});\n\n        assertThat(result).isEqualTo(Boolean.TRUE);\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void invokesProceedMethodForSubclassProxyNonCandidateMethod() throws Throwable {\n        final InvocationTarget proxyInstance = new InvocationTarget(\"self\");\n        final InterceptorMethodHandler handler = newHandler(null, InvocationTarget.class);\n        final Method thisMethod = Object.class.getMethod(\"toString\");\n        final Method proceedMethod = InvocationTarget.class.getMethod(\"proceedResult\");\n\n        final Object result = handler.invoke(proxyInstance, thisMethod, proceedMethod, new Object[] {});\n\n        assertThat(result).isEqualTo(\"proceeded:self\");\n    }\n\n    private static <T> InterceptorMethodHandler newHandler(Object targetInstance, Class<T> targetClass) {\n        final ClassMetadata<T> targetMetadata = ReflectiveClassMetadata.of(targetClass);\n        final InterceptionModel<ClassMetadata<T>, ?> interceptionModel = InterceptionModelBuilder\n                .newBuilderFor(targetMetadata)\n                .build();\n        final InterceptorInstantiator<Object, Object> interceptorInstantiator = interceptorReference -> {\n            throw new AssertionError(\"No interceptor instances are required for this non-intercepted method path\");\n        };\n        final InvocationContextFactory invocationContextFactory = null;\n        return new InterceptorMethodHandler(\n                targetInstance,\n                targetMetadata,\n                interceptionModel,\n                interceptorInstantiator,\n                invocationContextFactory);\n    }\n\n    public static final class InvocationTarget {\n        private final String name;\n\n        public InvocationTarget(String name) {\n            this.name = name;\n        }\n\n        public String proceedResult() {\n            return \"proceeded:\" + name;\n        }\n    }\n}\n"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1965, "output": 1630, "cacheRead": 24064, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 27659, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1778318996371, "responseId": "resp_077ccfdcb7edf56f0169fefe94e548819ca3ecc002af8ff4e1"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_F4OHQ0khVfulc65nNChCETTe|fc_077ccfdcb7edf56f0169fefea15f60819caf2ff02651657e9c", "toolName": "write", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Successfully wrote 3260 bytes to tests/src/org.jboss.interceptor/jboss-interceptor-core/2.0.0.CR1/src/test/java/org_jboss_interceptor/jboss_interceptor_core/InterceptorMethodHandlerTest.java"}], "isError": false, "timestamp": 1778319013281}]}
