[recv] {"type": "message_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Interpreting testing guidelines**\n\nI see that the guideline suggests keeping coverage for each dynamic-access class in its own dedicated Java test file. This means there should be a one-to-one mapping between the report classes and the generated test class files. It makes sense to avoid creating extra Java files, which would likely complicate the structure and organization of the codebase. I'll focus on understanding how to implement this effectively without adding unnecessary complexity.\n\n**Importing AtomicInteger**\n\nI need to import the AtomicInteger class to use it effectively in my code. The right way to do this is by specifying the path: `java.util.concurrent.atomic.AtomicInteger`. This is pretty straightforward, but, of course, I want to make sure that I don't miss anything or accidentally mess it up. It’s just about getting it right, and then I’ll be all set to use AtomicInteger as needed!", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_077ccfdcb7edf56f0169fefebb42f8819cb7f3fb92c0b0b385\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp_v7NZXlyyBQfAtDEpYjosYjXj8gYV6fliicOcsE-Cv5aSlnliLg6vkza9k0bkrAsH24ahSr_WQAM9YnSUauK8k15AMOYRkpjb3cBEN4lcKl6T1u2U73pLomtr-UU7TGkvsmW1Mi8fK1a_lRhJ_Z7hi-InOxEJJmld7zD-ev64UjopmSiH5nEKUviYb1-7cPdqa_Smw5jsSOuZy_94QZTX5eRY-u-KDqZMJdtr_XfqTnE3zbPWI9y84vztEZQuTgSmT8QaBiFRaYV66bYlrK-v9GcjgxDY6pLwMm_-orwpedGalemQAmGHkcJTqo6mXonspXHZ2kRYbBwlGVM3uAgIsGgDf98h1WiT6U0yXZgso7y3N88fYC7Us8EqE4BTWdB1vATp33wj2B4I1T1iIz5pAeOPUO6wvSuIE0HD-16Qdqpzeq30nLLiEp9ekBG60FRnY7CDIYtS5PE7vgiMPp_Tb3W3gLiPLp-9ywv1hLHRs1MD9xdRC1Qj_HEd9hlVoaJt22l0I9QbJZs6OhzvraMwSr_fXP_TrKZJQCUVbdW9knJ6gn3xxST_6ElNAx7la04TUFEqWCVvkH6n4eB3HF_VpOp-UjxCPpKTZKXafUOauWfn5B_nMsfy0KGyHNA6AyGdD9SAQkgrowAYd276qq-ptqWYQAtGGArnVmqVjyAQs2KKYSOPRjX1m1jHTN23ggcARAvKno6xgEXNSWlEZwmP0VkUQpkK024-x0RTicep6mP_BDiVddMFhGk1gTLN_0KndMglKBuxz3TbMtqzMgnOa-kubokf6eE_tM3HTdauozuRtn_rbymngH5BhC